  "text": "The Firefox Servo CSS style system integration is structured around several key C++ components in layout/style/:\n\n1. **ServoStyleSet (layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h and .cpp)**: This is the main entry point for style resolution. The ServoStyleSet class (line 107 of ServoStyleSet.h) manages the set of style sheets that apply to a document, backed by a Servo Stylist. It contains StyleSheets and orchestrates style computation through methods like RuleAdded, RuleRemoved, and RuleChanged.\n\n2. **RestyleManager (layout/style/RestyleManager.h and .cpp)**: This component schedules and manages style recalculation. The RestyleManager class (line 202 of RestyleManager.h) tracks restyle requests, maintains the restyle generation counter (line 212), and manages frame restyling through its ServoRestyleState helper class. It integrates with ServoStyleSet as a friend class.\n\n3. **ServoBindings (layout/style/ServoBindings.h)**: This header defines the Gecko-to-Servo FFI (Foreign Function Interface) declarations. It contains C FFI declarations (extern \"C\") with macros like BASIC_RULE_FUNCS_LOCKED and GROUP_RULE_FUNCS_LOCKED that generate Servo_* functions for rule handling, including functions like Servo_StyleSet_StyleRuleChanged, Servo_CssRules_GetStyleRuleAt, and many others for managing CSS rules at the Gecko-Servo boundary.\n\n4. **ServoUtils (layout/style/ServoUtils.h)**: This header provides utility functions for Servo traversal state management. Key functions include InitializeServo(), ShutdownServo() for initialization, and IsInServoTraversal() (line 24) which checks if we're currently in a Servo style traversal by examining the static sInServoTraversal pointer.\n\n5. **moz.build (layout/style/moz.build)**: This build configuration file lists all source files for the layout/style module. It exports all the key headers mentioned above and includes source files like ServoStyleSet.cpp (line 276), RestyleManager.cpp (line 271), and many others related to CSS style computation.\n\nThe style resolution pipeline flows through ServoStyleSet as the orchestrator, which coordinates with RestyleManager for change tracking and schedules restyling via the Servo engine through FFI bindings in ServoBindings. ServoUtils provides the thread-safety and traversal state infrastructure needed for this async style computation."
}

